# --- Build output (regenerable; excluded from version control) ---
# M33 single-build policy (DEC-0041): ONE canonical CMake tree at /build/.
# The /build*/ pattern also swallows any legacy per-agent tree (build-qa-*,
# build-m31-sdl, ...) so they can never reappear as repo noise — but creating
# them is itself a policy violation; agents must reuse /build/.
/build*/
build/
/build-*.log
*.o
*.obj
*.exe
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.lib
*.a
*.dll

# DEC-0030 exception: the fMSX 6.0 reference executable (human-provided
# cross-reference asset, references/fmsx-60/ -- NOT a build output).
!/references/fmsx-60/executables/fMSX.exe

# M53 (DEC-0080): the msx-diskutil host tool is a build product, post-build-copied
# from the ONE build/ tree; ignore the binary, keep the folder scaffolding.
# (The global *.exe rule already covers the .exe; the no-extension line covers
# the POSIX binary and is listed for discoverability.)
/utils/msx-diskutil
/utils/msx-diskutil.exe

# DEC-0097: the runtime settings file + File>Recent sidecar now live at the
# PROJECT ROOT (beside the assets they name, identical on every platform --
# the exe dir is build/Debug on Windows but build/ elsewhere). They are
# PER-MACHINE generated state: the emulator writes them, they carry absolute
# asset paths resolved on THIS machine, and committing one would push a
# Windows path onto the Mac/Pi and break their asset resolution. Never track.
/sony_msx_hbf1xv.xml
/sony_msx_recent.txt

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# CMake scratch
CMakeUserPresets.json
/cmake-build-*/

# --- Generated debug/trace runtime output ---
# The debug/ tree is created at runtime by the emulator (traces, logs, frames,
# audio). Keep the directory scaffolding but do not track generated captures.
/debug/**/*.trace
/debug/**/*.log
/debug/**/*.txt
/debug/**/*.png
/debug/**/*.wav
/debug/**/*.bin
/debug/**/*.dump
/debug/**/*.frame
/debug/**/*.script
/debug/**/frame_dump
/debug/**/emulator.out
/debug/**/emulator.log
# M36 playtest harness run dirs (timestamped, ephemeral capture output)
/debug/playtest_*/
# M36 Phase 3 comprehensive debug snapshots (per-component captures under
# debug/snapshot/<id>/ -- deterministic but regenerable runtime output; the
# blanket dir ignore also catches arbitrary-extension files like manifest.txt).
/debug/snapshot/
# DEC-0052 live stream-capture output: per-frame snapshot bundles under
# debug/snapshot/stream_<id>/ (already caught by /debug/snapshot/ above) and the
# per-instruction trace ring dump debug/traces/stream_<id>_trace.txt (already
# caught by /debug/**/*.txt above). Listed explicitly for discoverability.
/debug/snapshot/stream_*/
/debug/traces/stream_*_trace.txt

# NOTE: the former `!/debug/...` committed-evidence exceptions (M26/M27/M29/M31/
# M32, DEC-0029/0031/0034) were REMOVED in v1.7.0. They were dead rules: the
# local-only carve-out below excludes the whole `/debug/` DIRECTORY, and git
# cannot re-include a path whose parent directory is excluded -- so not one of
# them had any effect (zero debug/ files are tracked). They also named game
# titles in a PUBLISHED file, which contradicts the private-titles decision
# (DEC-0047-AMENDMENT-E). Debug captures are regenerable runtime output; evidence
# worth keeping lives in the local-only docs/ reports.

# --- Non-redistributable third-party assets: bios/, roms/, disks/ ---
# DEC-0093 (2026-07-18): the project no longer TRACKS OR PUBLISHES any proprietary
# BIOS/firmware/ROM/disk asset (see the IP notice in bios/README.md). This REVERSES
# DEC-0047's owner accepted-risk decision to host bios/ + the FM-PAC firmware on the
# public remote. Now untracked (git rm --cached; kept on the local filesystem):
#   - the seven Sony HB-F1XV BIOS ROMs   bios/*.rom
#   - the Panasonic FM-PAC firmware      roms/fmpac.rom
#   - its battery-save                   roms/fmpac.rom.sram
# Users provide their own BIOS/firmware images separately. Only the human-authored
# READMEs + .gitkeep markers stay tracked, so the directory skeleton is visible on the
# remote but empty of proprietary content.
# HISTORY: purged. DEC-0093-AMENDMENT-A (2026-07-18) rewrote EVERY commit and tag
# with git-filter-repo, so these binaries no longer exist anywhere in this
# repository -- not in the tip, not in history, not in any tag. Verified with
# `git rev-list --all --objects` returning zero .rom/.dsk/.sram blobs.
/bios/*
!/bios/.gitkeep
!/bios/README.md
/roms/*
!/roms/.gitkeep
!/roms/README.md
/disks/*
!/disks/.gitkeep

# Local game library at the repo root (user-provisioned game disks/roms, e.g.
# games/disks/<title>/*.dsk). DEC-0047-AMENDMENT-D (2026-07-18): the DIRECTORY
# SKELETON is exposed on the remote via .gitkeep markers (folder/title names
# visible), but every content file (.dsk/.rom/saves) stays untracked — the same
# non-redistributable, never-tracked policy as
# disks/ and roms/ -- provisioned locally, never committed or pushed.
# Only games/, games/disks/, games/roms/ (+ this README) are exposed on the
# remote; the per-title subfolders and every content file stay untracked
# (DEC-0047-AMENDMENT-E: title names are private).
/games/**
!/games/.gitkeep
!/games/README.md
!/games/disks/
!/games/disks/.gitkeep
!/games/roms/
!/games/roms/.gitkeep
# --- Editor / IDE / OS cruft ---
.vs/
*.user
.idea/
/.vscode/
.vscode/*.log
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# NOTE: bios/, roms/, disks/, and games/ hold third-party assets (Sony HB-F1XV BIOS
# ROMs, Panasonic FM-PAC firmware, cartridge ROMs, MSX-DOS disks) that remain their
# rights holders' property; this project asserts NO redistribution rights and makes no
# provenance claim. Per DEC-0093 (2026-07-18) NONE of these proprietary binaries are
# tracked or published -- only the human-authored READMEs + .gitkeep skeleton are on
# the remote; users provide their own BIOS/firmware/ROM/disk images locally (see the IP
# notice in bios/README.md). This REVERSES DEC-0047's public bios/ + FM-PAC hosting.
# The history was PURGED of them as well (DEC-0093-AMENDMENT-A): every commit and
# tag was rewritten, so no proprietary binary survives anywhere in this repository.
# Everything non-proprietary (references/, tests/, tools/, docs/, debug/, .claude/, etc.)
# is tracked per its own rules; the /debug/**/* pattern ignores above still apply
# (regenerable runtime captures untracked; committed evidence keeps its `!` exceptions).

# --- Local-only development apparatus (DEC-0082-AMENDMENT-B, 2026-07-16) ---
# The brief DEC-0082 publication of the coordination set (docs/, agent-protocol/,
# .claude/, CLAUDE.md files; pushed as 17fe2f3/ea5894a) was REVERSED by owner
# direction: removed from the remote TIP via `git rm -r --cached`. These trees are
# NON-proprietary project material, so the DEC-0093-AMENDMENT-A purge deliberately
# left them alone -- they may still appear in earlier commits, which is harmless.
# All of these stay fully present and usable on the LOCAL filesystem of both
# machines; cross-machine sync is by manual copy (recorded limitation).
# debug/'s pattern ignores + committed-evidence `!` exceptions above still apply.
#
# DEC-0099 (v1.7.0): tools/ is NO LONGER local-only -- it is PUBLISHED. It was
# first reorganised into purpose-folders (gates/ openmsx/ gen/ convert/ analyze/
# capture/ input-scripts/) with milestone numbers and GAME TITLES removed from
# every filename and from file contents, since game titles are private
# (DEC-0047-AMENDMENT-E) and publishing them would have undone the history scrub.
# DEC-0100 (v1.7.0): tests/ is NO LONGER local-only -- it is PUBLISHED. Keeping
# it hidden meant every cross-cutting refactor desynced the other machine (a
# renamed source dir, a retired test, a deleted header each broke the Mac build
# in turn), because a change to src/ and its matching change to tests/ could not
# land together. Tracking makes those atomic. The tree is project-authored: the
# tests/parity/ fixtures are SYNTHETIC probes generated by tools/gen/*, not
# proprietary images, and game titles were scrubbed from names and contents
# before publication (DEC-0047-AMENDMENT-E).
/.claude/
/agent-protocol/
/debug/
/docs/
/references/

# AI assistant memory files — local-only, hidden from the remote (owner request)
/CLAUDE.md
/src/CLAUDE.md
